Gitter is a third-party GitHub mobile client that supports iPhone and iPad. With Gitter, you can:
-Browse daily/weekly/monthly open source trend rankings in various languages ​​on GitHub to help you discover outstanding open source libraries and developers;
-View open source library source files/code;
-Conveniently discuss Issue and Pull request with developers;
-Fast Star, Watch, Fork open source library, Follow developers;
-Track and view the open source libraries you care about, and developer activity information;
-Search for the open source repositories and developers you want to find;
-View open source libraries and developers that you own/collect/follow;
-Modify most of the personal information;
- More......
-------------------------
If you have any suggestions or bugs, you can let me know through the feedback function of the APP, or you can directly enter https://github.com/gitterapp/gitterapp-feedback to submit issues to me.
If you think Gitter is pretty good, I hope you can give us a good comment to encourage you.
[]~(￣▽￣)~*
------------------------
Privacy note: Gitter will not collect any information from your GitHub account.
